Place chicken in large shallow dish. Combine vinegar, garlic, soy sauce, bay leaves, and ground red pepper; pour over chicken, turning to coat. Cover. Refrigerate 4 hours, turning occasionally. Transfer chicken and marinade to heavy skillet; add water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, turning occasionally. Remove chicken and set aside. Bring liquid to a boil; boil, uncovered, until reduced to 1/2 cup. Stir in chili; add chicken, turning to coat. Simmer until thoroughly heated.